<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-04-28T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-04-28T12:00:00-05:00" n="291" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d291">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">320.2–AC/4–2851: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">United States Mission at the United
                                    Nations</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-04-28T12:00:00-05:00">April 28,
                                    1951—noon</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>887. UK Emb informed Dept Apr 27 UK wld agree to <gloss target="#t_AMC1">AMC</gloss> mtg <pb facs="0519" n="1977" xml:id="pg_1977"/> Apr 30.
                            Added, however, UK wld object strongly to <gloss target="#t_AMC1">AMC</gloss> moving quickly and reporting at once to <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> First Comite. UK hopes <gloss target="#t_AMC1">AMC</gloss> will hold “occasional” mtgs and wishes
                            opportunity for further consultations like those now under way so that
                            prior to preparation <gloss target="#t_AMC1">AMC</gloss> report future
                            action may be reviewed in light circumstances then prevailing.</p>
                        <p>Emb reps were informed we were arranging <gloss target="#t_AMC1">AMC</gloss> mtg with Sarper, probably May 3. Dept reps naturally
                            agreed there must be full discussion of proposals but emphasized Dept
                            view <gloss target="#t_AMC1">AMC</gloss> shld now proceed to act.
                            Further details by pouch.</p>
                        <p>Reptd info AmEmbassy London 4953.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>